definition: Cryptococcus neoformans grows vegetatively as budding (unicellular) yeast but during the sexual cycle, switches from yeast growth to hyphal (multicellular) growth. This morphoogical development may be relevant to cryptococcal pathogenicity.
Crystal jelly, a bioluminescent hydrozoan jellyfish, or hydromedusa; source of 'Green Fluorescent Protein'(GFP).
barber's pole worm (a common parasite of ruminants).
bush baby; any of several species of small nocturnal arboreal primates (family Galagidae)
